Responsibility is in our very nature.


 
 



Energy Star Partner of the Year
In 2017, we were named U.S. EPA’s Energy Star® Partner of the Year. As our American manufacturing sites create life’s everyday essentials, we continually challenge ourselves to do more with less. We’ve invested $600 million into energy saving initiatives, and will continue to do so. Over the last five years, we’ve saved enough energy to power 360,000 households for an entire year.





Responsibility by the numbers.

It’s one thing to say we’re committed to environmental responsibility. But quite another to demonstrate it. Based on the latest Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) TRI National Analysis Report, 92% of the production related waste (PRW) our 124 reporting facilities produced in 2015 was recycled, recovered for energy or treated — a total of 605 million pounds. Review the TRI report for yourself here.







