Industrial Conglomerates

Company Overview of Koch Industries, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Koch Industries, Inc., through its subsidiaries, engages in the business of refining, chemicals, biofuels, and ingredients; forest and consumer products; fertilizers; polymers and fibers; process and pollution control equipment and technologies; electronic components; commodity trading; minerals; energy; ranching; glass; and investments worldwide. It produces transportation fuels, petrochemicals, ethanol, asphalts, base oils, gasoline, jet fuel, diesel, biodiesel, and heating oils; operates pipelines that transport crude oil, refined petroleum products, ethanol, natural gas liquids, and chemicals; and manufactures building and consumer products, tissue, packaging, paper, cellulose, and chemi...
Koch Industries, Inc., through its subsidiaries, engages in the business of refining, chemicals, biofuels, and ingredients; forest and consumer products; fertilizers; polymers and fibers; process and pollution control equipment and technologies; electronic components; commodity trading; minerals; energy; ranching; glass; and investments worldwide. It produces transportation fuels, petrochemicals, ethanol, asphalts, base oils, gasoline, jet fuel, diesel, biodiesel, and heating oils; operates pipelines that transport crude oil, refined petroleum products, ethanol, natural gas liquids, and chemicals; and manufactures building and consumer products, tissue, packaging, paper, cellulose, and chemicals. It produces chemical intermediates, polymers and plastics, fibers and fabrics, and specialty chemicals; manufactures antennas, application tooling, cable assemblies, connected lighting, connectors, copper flex, electrical products, industrial automation, membrane switches, optical solutions, and PCB assemblies for aerospace and defense, automotive, commercial vehicle, connected lighting, consumer/home appliance, data and computing, electrical/industrial, medical, industrial automation, scientific, smart phones and devices, energy, telecommunications/networking, and wireless infrastructure; produces fertilizers and plant nutrients; and produces methanol for use in daily products. It markets, trades, and handles dry-bulk commodities; engages in oil and gas exploration and production, oil field products, steel, and more; supplies and trades crude oil, refined petroleum products, natural gas, industrial metals, and other valued commodities; and operates ranches for breeding commercial cattle for beef products and horses for marketing to select forums. The company was formerly known as Rock Island Oil & Refining Co,. Inc. and changed its name to Koch Industries, Inc. in 1968. The company was founded in 1940 and is based in Wichita, Kansas with subsidiaries in the United States.
