Koch Industries, Inc. Key Developments

Koch Industries, Inc. Announces Executive Changes
Mar 3 17
Koch Industries Inc. has announced the promotion of key leaders to newly created positions within the company. Koch says in an emailed press release that Jim Hannan, president and CEO of the company's Georgia-Pacific unit, has been named executive vice president and CEO of enterprises. In addition, Brad Razook, president and CEO of Koch's Flint Hills Resources, has been named executive vice president and CEO of resources. In those new roles, Hannan will oversee Koch companies Georgia-Pacific, Invista, Molex and Guardian, as well as the recently acquired stake in business software and cloud computing company Infor. In other Koch executive news, the company said that Martin Slark, CEO of Molex, has been elected to the Koch Industries board of directors. The company also announced four appointments to the officer level at the company as follows: David Dotson - vice president, operations and compliance. Philip Ellender - vice president, government and public affairs. Matt Flamini - vice president, business development. Walt Malone - vice president, human resources.


Koch Industries, Inc. Presents at Annual ECO:nomics Conference, Apr-06-2016 through Apr-08-2016
Mar 2 16
Koch Industries, Inc. Presents at Annual ECO:nomics Conference, Apr-06-2016 through Apr-08-2016. Venue: Bacara Resort & Spa, 8301 Hollister Avenue, Santa Barbara, CA 93117, United States. Presentation Date & Speakers: Apr-07-2016, Sheryl Corrigan, Director of Environmental, Health and Safety.


Koch Interested In Acquiring Arrium's Moly-Cop
Aug 19 15
Koch Industries, Inc. is one of several international trade buyers looking at Moly-Cop division from Arrium Limited (ASX:ARI). Other potential acquirers include POSCO (KOSE:A005490), Gerdau S.A. (BOVESPA:GGBR4), FLSmidth & Co. A/S (CPSE:FLS) and Metso Corporation (HLSE:MEO1V).


